\ Exercises the text-mode crash handler in sandbox/debug.vfx (TermCrashProc).
\ Loads the handler, then deliberately triggers three kinds of fault, each via
\ CATCH so the run continues. Each should print the exception code, faulting
\ word, registers, and both annotated stacks, then recover.
\
\   Interactive:  ld test/crashtest
\   Headless:     drive via engineer/_ctest.vfx (output redirect + Win32Catch)
\
\ Win32Catch arms SEH->THROW for the current thread (the headless `include`
\ thread isn't armed by default; harmless interactively).

validations off ld %idir%/../sandbox/debug
Win32Catch

only forth definitions

variable n   0 n !
: run  ( xt -- )
    catch
    1 n +!
    cr ." [survived fault #" n @ . ." throw=" . ." ]" cr ;

\ 1) access violation: fetch from null, with sentinels on the data stack
: t1  $11111111 $22222222 $33333333 0 @ ;
' t1 run

\ 2) integer divide by zero. NOTE: literal `7 0 /` is constant-folded to a
\    COMPILE error, so tick `/` and run it via catch with divisor (TOS) = 0.
$AAAAAAAA $BBBBBBBB 7 0 ' / run

\ 3) faulted EXTERN: allegro fn dereferences garbage -> doExternExit recovery.
\    `^ engineer` puts the allegro words back in the search order.
^ engineer
: t3  $DEADBEEF al_get_bitmap_width ;
' t3 run

cr ." ===== ALL THREE EXCEPTIONS HANDLED, PROCESS ALIVE =====" cr
